.TH CC\-TOKEN\-SAVER\-MCP 1 "2026-06-26" "1.0.0" "CC Token Saver MCP"
.SH NAME
cc\-token\-saver\-mcp \- MCP server that delegates simple tasks to a local LLM
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cc\-token\-saver\-mcp
[\fB\-h\fR]
[\fB\-V\fR]
[\fB\-t\fR \fIMODE\fR]
[\fB\-\-host\fR \fIHOST\fR]
[\fB\-p\fR \fIPORT\fR]
[\fB\-m\fR \fINAME\fR]
[\fB\-\-base\-url\fR \fIURL\fR]
[\fB\-\-api\-key\fR \fIKEY\fR]
[\fB\-\-temperature\fR \fIFLOAT\fR]
[\fB\-\-max\-tokens\fR \fIN\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-banner\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cc\-token\-saver\-mcp
starts a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that exposes a locally running
LLM as tools for Claude Code to use.
By routing simple, well-defined subtasks to the local LLM, it reduces the
number of tokens consumed by Claude Code on repetitive or low-complexity
operations.
.PP
The server reads its configuration from a
.I .env
file in the working directory, or from environment variables.
Any value set via a command-line flag takes precedence over both.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show a help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show the program version and exit.
.TP
.BI \-t " MODE" ", \-\-transport " MODE
Transport protocol to use.
Valid values:
.RS
.TP
.B stdio
Standard I/O (default).
Used by Claude Code and most MCP clients.
.TP
.B http
HTTP server.
Requires
.B \-\-host
and
.B \-\-port
to be set if non-default values are needed.
.TP
.B sse
Server-Sent Events (legacy; prefer
.BR http ).
.RE
.TP
.BI \-\-host " HOST"
Hostname or IP address to bind for
.B http
or
.B sse
transport (default:
.IR 127.0.0.1 ).
.TP
.BI \-p " PORT" ", \-\-port " PORT
TCP port for
.B http
or
.B sse
transport (default:
.IR 8000 ).
.TP
.BI \-m " NAME" ", \-\-model " NAME
Local model name to request from the endpoint.
Overrides the
.B LOCAL_MODEL_NAME
environment variable.
.TP
.BI \-\-base\-url " URL"
Base URL of the OpenAI-compatible local API.
Overrides
.BR OPENAI_BASE_URL .
.TP
.BI \-\-api\-key " KEY"
API key sent to the local endpoint.
Overrides
.BR OPENAI_API_KEY .
.TP
.BI \-\-temperature " FLOAT"
Sampling temperature in the range 0.0\(en2.0.
Overrides
.BR LOCAL_LLM_TEMPERATURE .
.TP
.BI \-\-max\-tokens " N"
Maximum tokens per response.
Use
.B \-1
for no limit.
Overrides
.BR LOCAL_LLM_MAX_TOKENS .
.TP
.B \-\-no\-banner
Suppress the FastMCP startup banner.
Useful when running inside scripts or CI.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B OPENAI_API_KEY
API key sent to the local LLM endpoint (default:
.IR none ).
.TP
.B OPENAI_BASE_URL
Base URL of the OpenAI-compatible local LLM API
(default:
.IR http://localhost:1234/v1 ).
.TP
.B LOCAL_MODEL_NAME
Model name to request from the local endpoint
(default:
.IR qwen2.5-7b-instruct ).
.TP
.B LOCAL_LLM_TEMPERATURE
Sampling temperature for generation (default:
.IR 0.7 ).
.TP
.B LOCAL_LLM_MAX_TOKENS
Maximum tokens per response; \-1 means no limit (default:
.IR -1 ).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .env
Optional dotenv file loaded from the working directory at startup.
Command-line flags override values from this file.
.SH TOOLS EXPOSED
.TP
.B query_local_llm
Send a prompt to the local LLM.
Accepts an optional system message, temperature override, and max-tokens
override.
.TP
.B query_local_llm_with_context
Send a prompt together with additional context (e.g. a code snippet).
Supports built-in system-message presets for
.IR code_review ,
.IR documentation ,
.IR refactor ,
and
.IR general .
.TP
.B list_available_models
Return all model IDs available at the configured local endpoint.
Call this before
.B switch_model
to discover valid names.
.TP
.B switch_model
Switch the active model for all subsequent tool calls in the current session.
.TP
.B summarize_text
Summarize a long text or document.
Accepts a target word count and an optional focus aspect.
.TP
.B generate_commit_message
Generate a Conventional Commits-style git commit message from a
.B git diff
output.
.TP
.B generate_unit_tests
Generate unit tests for a code snippet.
Supports pytest, unittest, jest, go test, and other frameworks.
.TP
.B explain_code
Explain a code snippet in plain language.
Audience levels:
.IR beginner ,
.IR developer
(default), and
.IR expert .
.TP
.B translate_text
Translate text to a target language while preserving markdown and
code-block formatting.
.SH EXAMPLES
Show help and exit:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
cc\-token\-saver\-mcp \-\-help
.EE
.RE
.PP
Start with default settings (local LLM at port 1234):
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
cc\-token\-saver\-mcp
.EE
.RE
.PP
Override the model and endpoint:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
cc\-token\-saver\-mcp \-\-base\-url http://localhost:8080/v1 \-\-model llama3
.EE
.RE
.PP
Start as an HTTP server on all interfaces at port 9000:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
cc\-token\-saver\-mcp \-\-transport http \-\-host 0.0.0.0 \-\-port 9000
.EE
.RE
.PP
Typical Claude Code MCP configuration in
.IR ~/.claude.json :
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
"mcpServers": {
  "cc-token-saver": {
    "type": "stdio",
    "command": "cc-token-saver-mcp"
  }
}
.EE
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR python3 (1)
